We were excited to try this restaurant for Valentines day, as the reviews were very good. The atmosphere was drab and the food was bland. They had a “special” menu for Valentines Day, which was a scaled down version of their normal menu. We are pretty fast eaters. After ordering our appetizers, entrees, after dinner drinks and dessert, the server impatiently handed us the dessert and told us that we had to “wrap it up” because the next customers were waiting to be seated. In all of the years I have been eating in restaurants, no one has EVER been so rude. We were ordering food and drinks and it is not as though we were loitering around at our table chatting for an hour without spending money. DO NOT BOTHER EATING AT THIS TERRIBLE RESTAURANT. The food is lousy and the service was absolutely unacceptable.

If you're craving for good Italian nostalgia without having to drive to one of New York's little Italy's this is a very good choice.

My chicken francese had sauce that was congealed. My wife ordered the lobster ravioli, which tasted extremely fishy. Our waitress disappeared at times. The hostess forgot to ask if we had a reservation. The only reason I am giving it two stars is the garlic bread and the buss boy was helpful.

Came off the plane at Newark after a five hour plane ride from Oregon.  Heading home to CT we were desperate for some good Italian food...and we found it 😃. Lobster ravioli were cooked perfectly and served in a lovely pink sauce, shrimp scampi was served with an almost Spanish-style rice that wasn't cloying and cheesy...a perfect compliment. Broccoli rabe side was done tender and wasn't too bitter in a nice garlic and oil. We were not expecting the complimentary garlic bread and family style salad that was very nicely dressed and my husband enjoyed his cheese tortellini with vodka sauce. What a nice surprise after a long trip!  Service was excellent! They also valet parking after 5pm.  Will be making "In Napoli" our regular stop after the airport from now on.

We went on a weeknight.  A bruschetta appetizer and garlic bread were served while we waited for our order.  We ordered a bottle of wine which was served nicely.  The salad with house dressing was absolutely delicious.  We all agreed the highlight of the evening was the Chicken Sorrentino (which for some reason is not on the regular menu), but it melts in your mouth.  We would go back again just for this tasty dish!  The Sole Francaise had generous portions and was very tasty too. The Delmonico Steak special was disappointingly fatty in almost every bite, so the manager did adjust the bill.  My only other comment is that the valet parking left early for the evening and unfortunately the lot was very tight to maneuver out of.

Attending a work-related function here in the upper/larger room. Overall a great night with really good food and friendly attentive staff. For my main dish I had the Chicken Francaise It was really well prepared- I can't stand when restaurants try and hide over-cooked chicken w/ a lot of sauce- here the chicken was cooked perfectly and great sauce w/ the perfect amount of lemon, wine and butter. My co-workers seemed to have enjoyed their meals as well. Hope to be back some day.

I've eaten at Napoli a couple of times now, both for business dinners, as well as personal dinners, and each and every experience has been delightful. The service staff is extremely attentive and responsive, and the food always comes out delicious. I particularly am a big fan of their chicken parm! Even the bread they serve is great, and I always have to resist filling up completely on it.  The prices are very reasonable, and the location is convenient right in Fort Lee near the GWB as well. When I'm craving a classier Italian meal, I can never go wrong with Napoli! Consider me a fan.
